                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“And we know that the Son of God has come and has given us an understanding, that we may know Him who is true; and we are in Him who is true, in His Son Jesus Christ. This is the true God and eternal life.”
                                                                            <b>I John 5:20 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“They are not of the world, just as I am not of the world. Sanctify them by Your truth. Your word is truth. As You sent Me into the world, I also have sent them into the world. And for their sakes I sanctify Myself, that they also may be sanctified by the truth.”
                                                                            <b>John 17:16-19 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“I still have many things to say to you, but you cannot bear them now. However, when He, the Spirit of truth, has come, He will guide you into all truth; for He will not speak on His own authority, but whatever He hears He will speak; and He will tell you things to come.”
                                                                            <b>John 16:12-13 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Thomas said to Him, “Lord, we do not know where You are going, and how can we know the way?” Jesus said to him, “I AM  the way, the truth, and the life. No one comes to the Father except through Me.”
                                                                            <b>John 14:5-6 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10"> His desire for us is to know Him through the written word and through the living word. God wants us to know the truth. Jesus prayed for His disciples, asking God to "sanctify them by the truth; Your Word is truth" <b>(John 17:17) </b> The Bible helps us know and understand the truth about Him, ourselves, and life. The Holy Spirit is called the Spirit of truth, and He will lead us into all truth. <b>Ezekiel 36</b>b we are told He will give us a new heart, and will put a new spirit within us...He will take away the stony heart and give us a heart of flesh.  He will put His Spirit within us and cause us to walk in His statues and we will desire to be obedient.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Do you remember that special moment in time when you realized you were a sinner in need of the savior and He was right there with you and you knew it was your sin that put Him on the cross.  You surrendered to Him and His pure light overshadowed the darkness of your life.  You had just experienced and enter into full truth for the very first time.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Yes until this point in our lives we don’t have full truth.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Have you ever experienced a small child who is seemingly very quiet and you might ask, “what are you doing?”  With big eyes they put their hands behind their backs and say, “nuffin” (nothing).  Funny how we don’t have to be taught how to lie.  Only Christ is truth and through His spirit the only one who can lead us into all truth.  To know truth and to be fully truthful.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">As Thomas said to Jesus in <b>John 14</b> “we don’t know the way”, Jesus replied “I AM the way, the truth and the life.  No one comes to the Father except through Me.”
                                                                            Like Thomas we didn’t know the way.  He is the way to the Father, to forgiveness, to salvation, life eternal and life here more abundantly and to truth.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">We began this journey through these twelve attributes for the purpose with the hope of enhancing our perspective of our Lord God Almighty.  Father, Son and Holy Spirit three in one. As stated in day one we must know Him, His character as that is where our faith begins and ends.  When we have a balanced understanding of who God is, and of His character our trust in Him will flow naturally.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Truth will be found as we seek to commit ourselves and our ways to His way.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">If you are unsure of your salvation or know you have not fully surrendered to Christ and would like to commit or recommit today please fill this form
                                                                        </p>
